&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Tax Accountant on Datadog’s Finance team, you’ll play a critical role in supporting our global tax function. You&#39;ll work across international tax provision and compliance, indirect tax reporting, and a range of strategic tax projects that impact our rapidly scaling business. This role offers meaningful cross-functional collaboration with Accounting, Finance, and external advisors, providing exposure to leadership and the opportunity to enhance global tax operations through automation and process improvement. It’s a great fit for a proactive, detail-oriented professional looking to grow their career in a high-impact, fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;At Datadog, we place value in our office culture - the relationships and collaboration it builds and the creativity it brings to the table. We operate as a hybrid workplace to ensure our Datadogs can create a work-life harmony that best fits them.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the preparation of global tax provisions, including current and deferred tax calculations under ASC 740&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with international tax compliance across multiple jurisdictions in coordination with external advisors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage indirect tax (VAT/GST/SUT) compliance, including reviewing filings and supporting audits and inquiries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct tax research and analysis across international, indirect, and corporate tax topics; draft documentation to summarize findings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support global tax audits by preparing schedules, responding to requests, and working with stakeholders and advisors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Accounting and Finance to align processes and ensure accurate tax reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A CPA or chartered accountant (or working toward certification) with a degree in Accounting, Tax, Finance, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced with 3–6 years in public accounting (Big 4 or equivalent) and/or in-house corporate tax roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledgeable in U.S. and international corporate tax compliance, ASC 740, and indirect tax principles, with an interest in global reporting frameworks like OECD Pillar 2&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly detail-oriented with strong analytical and documentation skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong communicator and collaborator who works well across teams and time zones&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled in managing multiple projects and priorities in a dynamic, fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Datadog values people from all walks of life. We understand not everyone will meet all the above qualifications on day one. That&#39;s okay. If you’re passionate about technology and want to grow your skills, we encourage you to apply.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits and Growth:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous and competitive benefits package&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;New hire stock equity (RSUs) and employee stock purchase plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuous career development and pathing opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee-focused best in class onboarding&lt;/li&gt;
